ŠFrom Phil to Alina, my wife and love of my life.
For memories of lunches and moments shared
in Berkeley Square Mayfair and in
the London Town that we grew to love together
and call our home."═
╩in Loving Memory of BRIAN MIST Naturalist and Conservationist
For his Work and Dedication to the Park
Who Died 8th May 2002 - Age 65
Sadly missed by his wife Rosie and son Bradley and all his friends"╬
╦A Battersea girl with a heart of gold. cared for her parents growing old
She would always give her time to share, with anyone feeling in despair
When troubles seem to fill their day, helped to clear their problems away
The world is now a sadder place, without her kind and smiling face
In memory of Mabel Gladys Coote 1922-2017"Ž
╠IN TREASURED MEMORY OF MY DARLING HUSBAND
FRANIE DANIELS 25.10.1910 - 15.2.1992
HIS BUSINESS WAS IN MOUNT STREET
TOGETHER WE SHARED THIS SECRET GARDEN
FOR EVER AND ALWAYS AND ALL ETERNITY YOUR SHELAGH"┌
ūIn memory of
William, Marquess of Hartington
Coldstream Guards
Killed in action whilst serving with 5th Battalion
Belgium September 1944
This seat is given by his brother and sisters
Andrew, Elizabeth and Anne"Ō
